WEBVTT

00:04.705 --> 00:05.672 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.706 --> 00:06.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.707 --> 00:08.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.575 --> 00:10.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
We will be doing something very
rapidly having

00:10.911 --> 00:13.480 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to do with the security of our
country.

00:13.513 --> 00:18.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Blocked by the
courts, President
Trump considers next steps for
his controversial

00:18.852 --> 00:20.354 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
immigration policy.

00:20.387 --> 00:23.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then: taking on U.S.-Asian
relations.

00:23.757 --> 00:28.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president welcomes Japan's
prime minister
to the White House, while
dodging a potential

00:28.862 --> 00:30.864 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
rift with China.

00:30.898 --> 00:32.132 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And it's Friday.

00:32.165 --> 00:35.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
take on the
week's news.

00:35.502 --> 00:41.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Plus: From his beginnings in
Motown, to receiving
the prestigious Gershwin Award,
hit-maker

00:41.775 --> 00:46.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Smokey Robinson sits down with
Jeffrey Brown
to talk about a lifetime of
music.

00:46.580 --> 00:52.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SMOKEY ROBINSON, Musician: We
were not just
some artists who recorded for
the same label.

00:52.219 --> 00:53.654 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We were actually friends.

00:53.687 --> 00:54.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We were like brothers and
sisters.

00:54.821 --> 00:56.189 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We hung out.

00:56.223 --> 00:59.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have what we call the Motown
family, and
we have always had that.

00:59.993 --> 01:07.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:07.935 --> 01:10.771 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:10.804 --> 01:20.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
now says that
he may sign, in his words, a
brand-new order

01:20.514 --> 01:24.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on immigration as early as
Monday or Tuesday.

01:24.217 --> 01:29.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he also says he still
figures to win the
court battle over his initial
attempt to bar

01:29.890 --> 01:33.026 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
travelers from seven mostly
Muslim nations.

01:33.060 --> 01:38.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The federal court of appeals in
the Ninth
Circuit upheld a freeze on that
ban in a Thursday

01:38.632 --> 01:40.434 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ruling.

01:40.467 --> 01:44.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
John Yang reports that all of
this unfolded
as the prime minister of Japan
visited the

01:44.371 --> 01:46.306 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
White House.

01:46.340 --> 01:51.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: President Trump made
clear today
he's ready for the court fight
about his immigration

01:51.645 --> 01:54.781 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
order to be over, but he's not
waiting for
the final ruling.

01:54.815 --> 01:58.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
It shouldn't have taken this
much time, because

01:58.485 --> 02:01.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
safety is a primary reason.

02:01.254 --> 02:04.758 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of the reasons I'm standing
here today
is the security of our country.

02:04.791 --> 02:09.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we will be doing something
very rapidly,
having to do with additional
security for

02:09.629 --> 02:10.597 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our country.

02:10.630 --> 02:12.599 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You will be seeing that some
time next week.

02:12.632 --> 02:17.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In addition, we will continue to
go through
the court process, and
ultimately I have no

02:17.404 --> 02:19.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
doubt that we will win that
particular case.

02:19.539 --> 02:24.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Trump gave no
details of just
what that additional security
will be, but

02:24.444 --> 02:28.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said the dangers are clear,
though he wouldn't
give specifics about them
either.

02:28.915 --> 02:33.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: While I have been
president,
which is just for a very short
period of time,

02:33.387 --> 02:37.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have learned tremendous things
that you
could only learn, frankly, if
you were in

02:37.691 --> 02:41.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a certain position, namely
president.

02:41.228 --> 02:44.731 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there are tremendous threats
to our country.

02:44.765 --> 02:47.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will not allow that to
happen, I can tell
you that right now.

02:47.567 --> 02:49.403 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will not allow that to
happen.

02:49.436 --> 02:53.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: This morning, the
president took
to Twitter to call the appeals
court decision

02:53.373 --> 02:56.209 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not to reinstate his travel ban
disgraceful.

02:56.243 --> 03:02.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Three judges, two of them
nominated by Democrats,
one by a Republican, upheld a
restraining

03:02.482 --> 03:07.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
order put in place by a federal
judge in Seattle
one week ago today.

03:07.654 --> 03:13.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The appeals court said the
government didn't
provide adequate due process to
affected travelers,

03:13.093 --> 03:17.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and provided no evidence that
anyone from
the seven countries in the order
has been

03:17.297 --> 03:20.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
responsible for U.S. terror
attacks.

03:20.133 --> 03:25.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The judges also concluded the
administration
is unlikely to prevail in a
trial on the merits

03:25.372 --> 03:27.174 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the case.

03:27.207 --> 03:31.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Within minutes of the decision,
the president
told reporters it was political
and tweeted,

03:31.278 --> 03:33.447 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
"See you in court."

03:33.480 --> 03:36.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Washington state's attorney
general, who filed
the suit, said, bring it on.

03:36.983 --> 03:39.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB FERGUSON, Washington State
Attorney General:
We have seen the president in
court twice.

03:39.853 --> 03:41.188 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And we're two for two.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's number one.

03:43.190 --> 03:48.061 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, in my view, the future of
the Constitution
is at stake.

03:48.095 --> 03:52.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Senate Minority
Leader Chuck Schumer
tweeted that the president
should see the

03:52.099 --> 03:54.901 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
writing on the wall and abandon
the order.

03:54.935 --> 04:00.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary Clinton tweeted simply
"3-0," a reference
to the unanimous decision.

04:00.173 --> 04:04.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iraqi Prime Minister Haider
al-Abadi said
he asked Mr. Trump in a phone
call to lift

04:04.978 --> 04:07.314 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the travel ban for Iraqis.

04:07.347 --> 04:11.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some have worked as translators
for the U.S.
military and their lives might
be in danger

04:11.551 --> 04:13.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
if they stay in Iraq.

04:13.353 --> 04:19.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For now, with the ban on hold,
refugees and
others from all of the seven
affected nations

04:19.693 --> 04:22.162 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are free to enter the United
States.

04:22.195 --> 04:27.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in addition to the appeals
court ruling,
the administration faces dozens
of other legal

04:27.033 --> 04:29.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
challenges from around the
country.

04:29.569 --> 04:32.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang at the
White House.

04:32.739 --> 04:36.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Late today, there
was word
that the Trump administration
may be leaning

04:36.843 --> 04:41.248 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
against appealing the
restraining order to
the U.S. Supreme Court.

04:41.281 --> 04:46.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the White House chief of
staff said that
it may still be possible.

04:46.153 --> 04:50.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: Ohio
Governor John
Kasich delayed eight executions
in the face

04:51.024 --> 04:54.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of a court fight over the
state's lethal injection
process.

04:54.494 --> 04:59.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A federal judge found that
process unconstitutional,
but the state is appealing.

04:59.432 --> 05:04.538 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The governor's decision pushes
back the executions
to May, or later.

05:04.571 --> 05:09.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From Syria's President Bashar
al-Assad, an
apparent gesture to President
Trump.

05:09.442 --> 05:15.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has told Yahoo News the U.S.
is welcome
to send troops to Syria to
battle those that

05:15.515 --> 05:17.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he called terrorists.

05:17.417 --> 05:22.389 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But he also said in the
interview that his
permission is contingent on
Washington respecting

05:22.422 --> 05:24.257 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
his government's sovereignty.

05:24.291 --> 05:27.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BASHAR AL-ASSAD, President of
Syria: If you
want to start genuinely as the
United States,

05:27.827 --> 05:31.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to do so, it must be through the
Syrian government.

05:31.731 --> 05:36.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are here, we are the Syrians,
we own this
country as Syrians, nobody else.

05:36.570 --> 05:38.338 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nobody would understand it like
us.

05:38.371 --> 05:44.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So you cannot defeat the
terrorism without
cooperation with the people and
the government

05:44.644 --> 05:46.646 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of any country.

05:46.680 --> 05:51.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Assad said he
shares the priority
that President Trump places on
fighting terrorism,

05:51.685 --> 05:57.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but he rejected the idea of
establishing safe
zones for refugees inside Syria.

05:57.490 --> 06:04.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Australia, temperatures
soared to 117 degrees
in and around Sydney today, as
an extreme

06:04.397 --> 06:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
heat wave grips the country.

06:06.566 --> 06:11.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Major industrial energy users
shut down in
order to help prevent blackouts.

06:11.271 --> 06:15.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Beaches were packed with people
looking for
relief, while zoo animals cooled
off with

06:15.775 --> 06:18.245 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a hose-down and frozen treats.

06:18.278 --> 06:25.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Forecasters expect Saturday
could be the hottest
February day ever recorded in
Australia.

06:25.252 --> 06:29.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, Education
Secretary
Betsy DeVos faced protesters in
her first

06:29.789 --> 06:34.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
visit to a public school since a
bruising
confirmation fight.

06:34.060 --> 06:38.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Several dozen people tried to
block her from
entering a school in Washington.

06:38.098 --> 06:43.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She said later that she respects
peaceful
protest, but -- quote -- "will
not be deterred"

06:44.004 --> 06:45.438 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from doing her job.

06:45.472 --> 06:50.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DeVos has drawn fire for her
support of alternatives
to public schools.

06:50.076 --> 06:53.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Wall Street finished this Friday
on a high
note.

06:53.313 --> 06:58.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mining and energy stocks led the
way, as prices
for oil and copper jumped.

06:58.418 --> 07:04.391 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained nearly
97 points to close at 20269.

07:04.424 --> 07:09.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose almost 19, and
the S&amp;P 500
added eight.

07:09.095 --> 07:13.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the week, all three indexes
gained about
1 percent.

07:13.099 --> 07:18.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
President
Trump shifts his approach to
China; new revelations

07:18.805 --> 07:24.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in National Security Adviser
Michael Flynn's
relationship with Russia;
changes the newly

07:24.678 --> 07:34.721 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
confirmed health secretary could
make immediately;
and much more.

07:34.721 --> 07:41.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
confirmed health secretary could
make immediately;
and much more.

07:41.294 --> 07:45.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we mentioned earlier, the
prime minister
of Japan was at the White House
today, the

07:45.432 --> 07:48.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
beginning of several days of
talks with the
president.

07:48.535 --> 07:54.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The visit comes amid growing
concerns in Asia
over trade, over North Korea's
missile and

07:54.607 --> 07:58.645 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nuclear programs, and over China
flexing its
military muscle.

07:58.678 --> 08:04.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
The bond between our two nations
and the friendship

08:04.551 --> 08:07.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
between our two peoples runs
very, very deep.

08:07.821 --> 08:12.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The two leaders
presented a
united front, despite
differences that have

08:12.959 --> 08:16.496 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
emerged in the early days of the
Trump presidency.

08:16.529 --> 08:22.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Prime Minister Shinzo Abe had
pushed hard
for the 12-nation Trans-Pacific
Partnership,

08:22.335 --> 08:25.438 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
but President Trump has
officially abandoned
it.

08:25.472 --> 08:32.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: On the economy, we
will seek
a trading relationship that is
free, fair,

08:32.178 --> 08:35.849 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and reciprocal, benefiting both
of our countries.

08:35.882 --> 08:40.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHINZO ABE, Japanese Prime
Minister (through
translator): I am quite
optimistic that good

08:40.854 --> 08:43.289 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
results will be seen from the
dialogue.

08:43.323 --> 08:47.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now the free and fair common set
of rules
will be created for free trade
in the region.

08:47.560 --> 08:49.529 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That was the purpose of TPP.

08:49.562 --> 08:51.264 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That importance has not changed.

08:51.297 --> 08:53.099 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I, myself, believe that.

08:53.133 --> 08:59.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Abe also talked
up Japanese
industry's contributions to the
U.S. economy,

08:59.172 --> 09:06.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after Mr. Trump blasted Toyota
last month
for planning a new plant in
Mexico.

09:06.312 --> 09:08.815 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Defense is another potential
flash point.

09:08.848 --> 09:14.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the campaign, candidate
Trump suggested
Japan and South Korea could pay
more for their

09:14.821 --> 09:18.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
own defense, up to and including
nuclear weapons.

09:18.525 --> 09:19.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: North Korea has
nukes.

09:19.993 --> 09:21.761 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Japan has a problem with that.

09:21.795 --> 09:23.530 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, they have a big problem
with that.

09:23.563 --> 09:27.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Maybe they would in fact be
better off if
they defend themselves from
North Korea.

09:27.033 --> 09:28.368 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
QUESTION: With nukes?

09:28.401 --> 09:31.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Including with
nukes, yes, including
with nukes.

09:31.471 --> 09:34.441 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Today, however,
the president
appeared to step back.

09:34.474 --> 09:40.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: It is important
that both Japan
and the United States continue
to invest very

09:40.280 --> 09:43.783 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
heavily in the alliance to build
up our defense.

09:43.817 --> 09:50.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Some 50,000 U.S.
troops are
stationed in Japan, the largest
American outpost

09:50.390 --> 09:52.025 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in Asia.

09:52.058 --> 09:57.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, Secretary of Defense
James Mattis
made Asia his first overseas
visit.

09:57.897 --> 10:03.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Japan, he reassured Abe that
the U.S. will
maintain its presence there.

10:03.803 --> 10:09.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. military also serves as
the main
counterweight to China's
increasing aggressiveness

10:09.876 --> 10:11.711 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the South China Sea.

10:11.744 --> 10:15.215 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today, Abe said that must
continue.

10:15.248 --> 10:19.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHINZO ABE (through translator):
We need to
maintain the freedom of
navigation and rule

10:19.819 --> 10:20.887 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of law.

10:20.920 --> 10:23.323 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Such international order there
must be maintained.

10:23.356 --> 10:29.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Hours earlier,
President Trump
spoke by phone for the first
time with China's

10:29.128 --> 10:31.664 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
President Xi Jinping.

10:31.698 --> 10:38.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the call, Trump retreated
from earlier
talk of disregarding the one
